Memory map

Purpose:
- Configuration-specific memory map for active `.uai`, local durable docs, MATM routes, and companion documentation.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with `.uai/long-term-memory.uai`, `.uai/long-term-pointer-ledger.uai`, and route evidence before relying on it.
Memory scope: memory layers, routing, durable targets, and truth boundaries.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains route names and paths only, no credentials.
Update route: update this map when memory layers, durable targets, setup modes, or route boundaries change.
Source of truth: `.uai/totem.uai`, `.uai/long-term-memory.uai`, `.uai/long-term-pointer-ledger.uai`, and MemoryEndpoints.com route contracts.
Next action for agents: choose the correct memory layer before writing or retrieving project facts.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, raw private memory bodies, or private workspace identifiers.

Memory layers:
- Active startup memory: `.uai/` files in the startup-packet read order.
- Human/agent front door: `AGENTS.md`, `workspace.uai`, and `.uai/readme.human`.
- Active dropped-file intake: `agent-file-handoff/Content` and `agent-file-handoff/Improvement`.
- Reviewed local durable memory: `docs/long-term-memory/` and `docs/reports/`.
- Hosted durable MATM: MemoryEndpoints.com protected routes when authenticated.
- Database-backed knowledge wiki: protected `matm_crawl_sources` and `matm_search_documents` rows exposed through `/knowledge`, `/api/matm/knowledge-tree`, and `/api/matm/knowledge-documents`.
- Public companion docs: MultiAgentMemory.com source under `sites/multiagentmemory.com/`.

Rules:
- Durable memory augments active `.uai`; it never retires local `.uai`.
- `.uai` contains pointers and current operating state, not raw secrets or long report bodies.
- README.md files are human documentation, not memory-package state.
- Research/report intake is processed one file at a time. For each report, create one reviewed wiki document at company/workspace/project scope, then create one compact MATM memory summary that links back to that wiki source. Do not bulk-import archives.
- Every wiki knowledge document needs a title, description, keywords, and one or more taxonomy paths. Exact search is not enough; agents must be able to browse contextual hierarchy paths such as `AI infrastructure > tokenization > prompt optimization`. One canonical document can appear in multiple hierarchies without duplicating the stored body.
